title: Sustainable & Ethical streetwear brand need creative luxury logo that you'd love to wear and support
name_to_incorporate: Maclyn Apparel wordmark & separate M + A monogram
description:
We are a casual lifestyle streetwear brand looking to professionally present a deep-rooted and modern culturally artistic impression to the public, our clientele, and other businesses.
**Update-3**
Both the Word-mark & Monogram need to be Powerful Typography and should be a "stand-alone" attention-grabbing, memorable piece. It is to complement any canvas it is applied to which embodies the ideas, passion, creativity, and mission of our brand identity.
**Nothing should have shape edges or the appearance of a mountain. Take note, there's both monogram but also a separate letter-mark. Both should have similarities but are stand-alone pieces. Including mocks up both in black and white and having both designs together and apart is a very strong visual plus, thank you!
***These designs are not for the corporate world, even though they should have an upscale look. Keep the direction focused on urban streetwear, rather than a corporate company.
**If color is added great but black & white are primary and finished project needs to have the options to fill in colors when needed.
**When designing, the letter-mark "Maclyn" do keep in mind it should be the focal point of the design that is separate from the monogram yet similar in look and isn't covered up by the optional add-on "Apparel" when adding to the letter-mark.
***In the finished version, all sections or parts of the design needs to be able to have their color changed individually and can place an image in the text.
When designing the Word-mark keep in mind this is going to be placed in large print on such apparel as sweaters, hats, hoodies, t-shirts, handbags, underwear, socks, jackets, pants for men and women. It must be a unique look that represents Hip-Hop and Surf culture with elements of punk, skateboarding, sportswear and some Japanese fashion.
Please include curves, 3D/2D or some kind of dimension to both designs. Nothing too sharp, too wide or too flat or plain with an effect mentioned below.
It is also an essential support symbol that represents these limited listed words e.g., Confidence, Bold, Creative, Modern, Harmony, Ambitious, Powerful, Genuine, Unique, Vibrant, Friendly, Clean, Iconic, Urban, Beauty, Powerful, Disruptive, Inspired, Energetic, Abstract, Smart, Expressive, Chic, Timeless, Character, Bright, Quality, Heritage, Premium, Cool, Hip, Cultured, Artistic, Movement, Transform, Rising from nothingness, Rebirth, Regeneration, Rising sun, A new day, Fresh beginnings, rising from the ashes.
Included is a reference sketch that does not need to be used, that was done for our Maclyn Apparel Word-mark and M+A monogram.
It isn’t clean, straight, or pronounced with the initials but has the open space within to add a layover design, later on, is different from other apparel brand logos and has potential as a base to build onto.
Globally iconic inspiration references - Stüssy, The Hundreds, Ralph Lauren Polo, Gucci, Levi’s, Off-White, Nike & BAPE - A Bathing Ape.
The finished project is to be recognized as having a clean high-end appearance and pays homage to creative urban streetwear cultural artwork by all, but our specific audience is Gen Y, Gen Z and Gen X and years range from the ’90s to modern-day and these designs are going to be used for years to come, so they should also have a timeless look and feel with a 1 to 2 color combination minimum for shading, adding another image, so the front isn’t hidden and other advantages.
We are not looking for anything ordinary or predictable, nothing typical, safe, generic, or a design that blends in with most of the apparel companies. Previously used templates, concepts, and or stock images are not to be used here. The design needs to be unique in and of itself and easily recognized.
We appreciate the smooth, wide, boldness, and edges of a San serif over a Serif but, jazz it up, get it hype! Add your clean artistic creative drip and swag, nothing plain, please! So give it some life, some character and Go wild!!!!
Manipulation of typography and or image may be altered and added to - like cut, stretch, tilt, wave, distortion, glitch, geometric and graffiti, etc. is ideal and a plus to the urban streetwear art culture image we’re looking to achieve.
Additionally, fonts such Futura, Valencia, Future X, Clarendon, Dassie, Extenda, Gravtrac, The love for money and built tilting are some great to use and customize to not be standard!
Although we are still in the process of researching a mascot or other symbols, this word-mark & monogram will do for now and the chosen designer may be contacted for that next project.
other_notes: Included are additional reference only designs that are not to be copied

Motivation for False-Motivation.com Coffee beans
description:
We are a coffee company that sells to military veterans, police officers, firemen, and motivated coffee drinkers.
I want to rebrand with enough character in the logo and branding that people want to express their own personality with a branded sticker or a branded t-shirt.
other_notes:
I do not like my current logo - https://false-motivation.com/
I plan to drop the brand down to a single coffee flavor.
The label is fairly generic the new logo will sit inside the white area(where the current logo sits) of the sticker that will be put on to the product. The company is a dropshipping company.
Due to dropshipping requirements, the only thing I can change in this label is what fits in side the white area, aka my logo.
------------------------------------------
FALSE MOTIVATION DEFINED
"False Motivation" is a motivation statement intended to be yelled at the top of your lungs when you're unable to find the real motivation to dig deeper into your soul and pour more motivation out when you do not have anything left to give.
This is a mindset many other Marines and myself learned during our time serving in the United States Marine Corps.
When you need to muster up the motivation to face the task that you do not have any motivation to face, you scream "False-Motivation" and run at the task with 110%.
This is the deep driving sense that allows United States Marines to be the BADASS'S they are, the ability to keep going when there is nothing left to give is why you choose Marines over anything else.
This is why I created the brand, False-Motivation, aka fake motivation. To remind me daily, to remind yourself daily, we have responsibilities that need to get handled whether we have the motivation or not.
We know the motivation that coffee brings you is a lie but it is a lie that is required to tell yourself. A lie to push you over that motivational ditch and climb that hill of motivation.
False-Motivation is the false God of Motivation but still just as inspiring.
So next time you walk into a meeting, give a little shoutout as you are about to sit down, "Motivation!". I promise you, the first few times people will look at you, just smile back. After a couple of times, your entire meeting will say it back and it will quickly become a thing.
Here at False-Motivation, it is our life mission to help you find the motivation and when you can not muster it up yourself, pour a cup of coffee and fake it with a smile on your face.
Love, some knuckle-dragging United States Marine
